  "prompt": "How can I use two WhatsApp accounts with the same number on different devices?",
  "response": "Using two WhatsApp accounts with the same phone number on different devices is not officially supported by WhatsApp. WhatsApp ties your account to a single phone number and is designed to work on one primary device at a time. However, there are a few workarounds you can try:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Use WhatsApp Web or WhatsApp Desktop**\n   - You can use WhatsApp Web (via a browser) or WhatsApp Desktop (via the app) on a second device to mirror your primary WhatsApp account.\n   - Steps:\n     1. Open WhatsApp on your primary device.\n     2. Go to **Settings** > **Linked Devices**.\n     3. Scan the QR code displayed on the second device using your primary device.\n   - Limitation: This is not a separate account but just a mirror of your primary account.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Use WhatsApp Business**\n   - You can install WhatsApp Business on a second device and register it with the same phone number.\n   - Steps:\n     1. Install WhatsApp Business on the second device.\n     2. Verify your phone number (same as your personal WhatsApp).\n   - Limitation: WhatsApp may eventually prompt you to choose which device to keep active.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Use Multiples Apps with App Cloners**\n   - Some Android devices or third-party apps allow you to clone WhatsApp, enabling you to use two instances of WhatsApp on the same device.\n   - Examples: **Parallel Space**, **Dual Apps**, or **App Cloner**.\n   - Steps:\n     1. Install a cloning app.\n     2. Clone WhatsApp and log in with your number.\n   - Limitation: This is not officially supported and may violate WhatsApp\u2019s terms of service.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Use Dual SIM Phones**\n   - If your phone supports dual SIM cards, you can use two separate phone numbers for two WhatsApp accounts on the same device.\n   - Steps:\n     1. Install WhatsApp and verify the first number.\n     2. Clone WhatsApp (if supported by your device) or install WhatsApp Business.\n     3. Verify the second number.\n   - Limitation: Requires two phone numbers.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Use a Secondary Number (Best Option)**\n   - The simplest and most reliable way to use two WhatsApp accounts is to use a secondary phone number.\n   - Steps:\n     1. Get a secondary number (via a second SIM card, VoIP service, or virtual number).\n     2. Install WhatsApp on the second device and verify the secondary number.\n\n---\n\n### **Important Notes**\n- Using unofficial methods (like cloning apps) may lead to account bans or security risks.\n- WhatsApp does not support using the same number on two devices simultaneously unless one is a linked device (WhatsApp Web/Desktop).\n\nIf you need two separate WhatsApp accounts, consider using a second phone number.",
